One cannot perform issue validation or enforce business rules upon Edit/QuickEdit. It would be great if JIRA exposed a callback interface that would be called on ticket modification. My idea is to have something like this:
{code:java}
public interface TicketModificationValidator{
    
    /**
    * The method is called when the ticket content is modified. If the method throws exception, the modifications to the ticket will not be applied.
    *
    * @param ticketCtx - contains the information about the original, unmodified ticket and provides means to perform additional modifications to it
    * @param modifications - contains the information about the performed changes to the ticket - i.e. added/removed components, changed field values, etc
    * @param userCtx - contains information about the user who executed the action
    *
    *@throws ValidationException - thrown to indeicate that the requested modifications to the ticket are invalid according to the business rules enforced by this validator.
    */
    void ticketModified(TicketContext ticketCtx, Modifications modifications, UserContext userCtx) throws ValidationException;
}{code}

